1. Introduction
This project is developed as part of the flipped course evaluation under the ‚ÄúBuild Your Own Project‚Äù initiative.
The main objective is to enable students to apply theoretical knowledge to a practical, real-world problem by designing, implementing, and documenting a complete working system.
________________________________________
2. Problem Statement
The project aims to solve a specific identified problem by offering a functional technical solution. The problem is analysed from the perspective of user needs, workflow inefficiencies, or automation requirements.
________________________________________
3. Functional Requirements
The system includes at least three major functional modules, such as:
1.	User Management
2.	Data Input & Processing
3.	Reporting / Output Generation
Each module has a clear input-output flow, ensuring a logical user interaction process.
